==English==

===Etymology===
Greek μουοφυδίής, “single nature”

====Noun====
'''monophysism'''
#A [[heresy]] which holds that the [[divinity]] in [[Christ]] is fused with his human nature and therefore he was divine as well as human, as opposed to the [[orthodox]] view that [[God]] took human form in the body of Christ. The doctrine of [[incarnation]] that is now commonly agreed upon - that Christ was both fully human and fully God - was formalized as the [[Nicene Creed]] in the 4th century in Nicea.

====Related terms====
[[monophysite]]
*Monophysites are called [[copt]]s [[Copt]]s in Egypt.
*Monophysites are called [[jacobite]]s [[Jacobite]]s in Syria and Palastine.

